Register iPad app
1. Generate a unique id for a device (https://github.com/gekitz/UIDevice-with-UniqueIdentifier-for-iOS-5)
2. Generate a pair of public/private key, store the private key to Keychain
3. Send the device id and the public key to server
4. Server will check if the device key is already registered, if not, then add to the user's devices list. (Also limit a number of devices per user)
5. Server will also keep the public key of this user (one public key per user device)
6. Server will generate 

Download Publication
1. App will send a secret key to server




1. Register iPad app by generating a unique id for a device and send it to server
2. By downloading a publication, server will send an encrypted publication along with a master key that was used to encrypted the publication. (The publication is sent by HTTP protocol but a master key is sent by HTTPS protocol)
3. A device will generate an user key 

